posts.description:
هتستفد ايه من حضور Imagine Cup Academy؟
- هيكون فيه ناس متخصصين منهم ناس من Microsoft هيكلمو معاكو على حاجات كتير ممكن تكونو عايزين تعرفوها.
-هيكون عندوكو الفرصة أنكو يكون ليكو Mentor  فى المشروع بتعكو ودة بيبقى شخص متخصص لكل فريق عشان يرشدو ويساعد ال فريق أنه ينجح. 
- موفرين ليكو المواصلات، buses الجامعة البريطانية هتوصلكو من مكان ما انتو سكنين  لحد باب الجامعة وترجعكو تاني كمان.
-هتتعلمو حاجات كتير جديده…
*المؤتمر ده لكل طلاب مصر وكل الجامعات!
*التسجيل عن طريق اللينكات في-description بتاع الافنت وتابعو الصفحة لمعلومات 
أكتر: https://www.facebook.com/events/550986975082558

What are the benefits of attending Imagine Cup Academy?
-There will be a lot of experts and Microsoft Professionals to talk about many things that you might want to know.
-You’ll get the chance to have a mentor to help you with your project that is dedicated to your team having a goal that is to help you Win the Imagine Cup competition.
-Transportation will be provided by the BUE busses, will transport your from your home to the university and the opposite.
-You’ll learn a lot more things…
*The conference is open for Bueians and out comers too!
*The registration is through the links provided in the description of the event, for more information check the event page: https://www.facebook.com/events/550986975082558

Share and invite everyone!

posts.message:
I found this article interesting, and thought I would 

This is Microsoft admitting its mobile strategy was a failure
Or, to be more accurate about it, it’s the final page in the chapter labeled “Windows Phone”. Having admitted that the Nokia purchase was a bad one, having admitted that Windows Phone wasn’t the success they wanted it to be, Microsoft is now (finally!) looking to recircle the wagons. The Lumia phones simply weren’t selling, and while I certainly know a number of people personally who love their Windows Phone, almost all of them are either Microsoft employees or relatives of Microsoft employees. Sales figures certainly seemed to agree with my understanding of consumers’ dislike of the devices, compared to iOS and Android.
